experimenting with it seamless.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"when-this-feature-works-best-and-when-to-skip-it\"\u003e\n                        When This Feature Works Best and When to Skip It\n               \u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n    \n\n\n\n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                \n    \n\u003cp\u003eSpot Color shines in specific situations. It’s not something you’ll want to use on every photo, but when the conditions are right, it can elevate an ordinary image into something visually striking.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch3 id=\"when-spot-color-works-best\"\u003e\n            When Spot Color Works Best\n    \u003c/h3\u003e\n\n                \n    \n    \n    \n                \n    \n                \n        \n                                                            \n                                                                                                                        \n                                        \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/06/whatsapp-image-2025-06-03-at-7-08-14-pm-3.jpeg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;Tyler Fyock\\/MakeUseOf\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n 